THE AIRCRAFT LOST POWER DURING TAKEOFF CLIMB AND WAS LANDED STRAIGHT 
AHEAD RESULTING IN SUBSTANTIAL DAMAGE. THE FUEL SELECTOR VALVE WAS 
HARD TO MOVE AND DURING TESTS MOVING IT CAUSED THE ENGINES TO QUIT. 
PIPER AD 80-18-10 WARNS THAT SCOTT MANUFACTURED SELECTOR VALVES "COULD 
CAUSE POWER LOSS DUE TO MALFUNCTION OF THE VALVES". DISASSEMBLY OF THE 
VALVE ON THIS AIRCRAFT REVEALED SCRAIR TRAFFIC CONTROLH MARKS ON THE SLIDING PORTION 
INDICATIVE OF BINDING. 
